A collection of required countries meta to be imported anywhere. The gist file is a comprehensive, ready-to-import collection of country metadata. It contains an array of 250 countries, each with the following fields:  code: ISO country code (e.g., "ES") name: Country name in English native: Country name in the native language phone: List of international dialing codes continents: List of continent codes (e.g., ["EU"]) capital: Capital city currency: List of currency codes languages: List of language codes used in the country language_names: List of full language names (resolved from codes) flag: Object with emoji, unicode, and image URL for the country flag This structure is clean, deduplicated, and suitable for direct import into any project needing country metadata for lookups, dropdowns, localization, or display.
